Therefore, if you change the technology and the constant costs change,

29:04.000 --> 29:07.000
this requires further study.

29:07.000 --> 29:15.000
It is impossible to answer whether the marginal profit will improve.

29:15.000 --> 29:19.000
The short-term marginal profit may decrease,

29:19.000 --> 29:24.000
and the total marginal profit for the entire service life of equipment may be greater.

29:25.000 --> 29:32.000
It is very important to pay attention to the goal of the owner of the enterprise.

29:32.000 --> 29:36.000
Do you want to get the maximum profit in one day?

29:36.000 --> 29:42.000
Or do you want to get the maximum profit for the entire service life of your enterprise?

29:42.000 --> 29:48.000
What is the goal of your business?

29:48.000 --> 29:53.000
Based on this, you can build up the costs of changing the technology.

29:53.000 --> 29:57.000
The point of non-profitability, which characterizes the production process,

29:57.000 --> 30:03.000
and which is very important for us, as we have just seen, can be calculated accurately.

30:03.000 --> 30:08.000
There are formulas for this, which you can see on the screen.

30:08.000 --> 30:13.000
The point of non-profitability in a natural way means the amount of products

30:13.000 --> 30:20.000
that the enterprise must produce in order to be not in loss,

30:20.000 --> 30:26.000
in order to be able to say that the revenue and the costs coincided.

30:26.000 --> 30:29.000
Yes, the profit is zero, but it is not a loss.

30:29.000 --> 30:34.000
So, the point of non-profitability in the quantitative expression is equal to

30:34.000 --> 30:39.000
the fraction in the numerator of the production of the constant costs per unit of the product,

30:39.000 --> 30:44.000
multiplied by the number of produced products, and in the denominator the marginal profit.

30:44.000 --> 30:52.000
Thus, the amount of products that must be produced in order to be not in loss is determined.

30:52.000 --> 31:00.000
You can stop the lecture once again and ask your economist,

31:00.000 --> 31:02.000
how many products do you produce?

31:02.000 --> 31:07.000
Now you know how many of them must be produced in order to be not in loss.

31:07.000 --> 31:10.000
The same formula is only in the constant expression.

31:10.000 --> 31:15.000
That is, in the monetary expression, not in the quantity of the products.

31:15.000 --> 31:18.000
Again, look at the screen.

31:18.000 --> 31:22.000
The point of non-profitability in the quantitative expression is equal to

31:22.000 --> 31:27.000
the fraction in the numerator of the production of the constant costs per unit,

31:27.000 --> 31:31.000
multiplied by the revenue, and divided by the marginal profit.

31:31.000 --> 31:36.000
I would like to draw your attention to the fact that these formulas are fair

31:36.000 --> 31:42.000
only for a company that produces one type of product.

31:42.000 --> 31:48.000
If there are many types of products at a company, the formula becomes somewhat complicated.

31:48.000 --> 31:50.000
Although the logic remains the same.

31:50.000 --> 31:57.000
You just need to consider several types of products, sum them up,

31:57.000 --> 32:04.000
and consider the point of non-profitability in relation to each of the types of produced products.

32:04.000 --> 32:09.000
After we have studied the point of non-profitability,

32:09.000 --> 32:17.000
I would like to emphasize that everything we are discussing today is not just a theory.

32:17.000 --> 32:21.000
This is a practice that must be tested.

32:21.000 --> 32:26.000
It is necessary to look at how the production is in your company.

32:26.000 --> 32:30.000
How much do you produce?

32:30.000 --> 32:33.000
How far have you moved away from the point of non-profitability?

32:33.000 --> 32:36.000
Or maybe you haven't even approached it yet?

32:36.000 --> 32:41.000
Depending on where you are in relation to the point of non-profitability

32:41.000 --> 32:46.000
and where you are moving towards the point of non-profitability or away from it,

32:46.000 --> 32:50.000
the management decisions depend on it.

32:50.000 --> 32:54.000
The management decisions will be completely different

32:54.000 --> 33:00.000
depending on where you are in relation to the point of non-profitability.

33:00.000 --> 33:03.000
If you are on the right side of the point of non-profitability,

33:03.000 --> 33:07.000
and the volume of your products is increasing, you should be happy.

33:07.000 --> 33:10.000
You can have a holiday at the company.

33:10.000 --> 33:14.000
This means that your marginal profit is growing,

33:14.000 --> 33:17.000
and things are going well at the company.

33:17.000 --> 33:21.000
If you are on the right side of the point of non-profitability,

33:21.000 --> 33:27.000
but the dynamics of production is such that the volume of products is decreasing,

33:27.000 --> 33:31.000
and you are moving to the point of non-profitability on the right,

33:31.000 --> 33:34.000
this is a disturbing symptom.

33:34.000 --> 33:40.000
Now we will look at another practical application of the material we have just discussed.

33:40.000 --> 33:46.000
So, we say that the more to the right we are from the point of non-profitability,

33:47.000 --> 33:52.000
the better our enterprise is doing economically.

33:54.000 --> 33:56.000
What does it mean?

33:56.000 --> 34:02.000
It means that the company has a reserve of financial strength.

34:02.000 --> 34:06.000
It has more and more profit, which it receives.

34:06.000 --> 34:10.000
And, accordingly, if it receives as much profit as possible,

34:10.000 --> 34:14.000
then its financial strength increases.

34:14.000 --> 34:18.000
The reserve of financial strength shows how much percentage

34:18.000 --> 34:22.000
the volume of the implementation can be reduced or increased

34:22.000 --> 34:27.000
to maintain or achieve the surplus level of work.

34:29.000 --> 34:34.000
The reserve of financial strength is very important for the enterprise.

34:34.000 --> 34:37.000
The enterprise should feel confident in business,

34:37.000 --> 34:42.000
so the reserve of financial strength should be as much as possible.

34:42.000 --> 34:46.000
The reserve of financial strength is mathematically defined

34:46.000 --> 34:52.000
as the absolute deviation from the point of non-profitability to the profit.

34:52.000 --> 34:57.000
We should look at how far our production volume

34:57.000 --> 35:03.000
exceeds the volume at which there is a point of non-profitability,

35:03.000 --> 35:09.000
and divide this excess into the profit that the enterprise has.

35:10.000 --> 35:14.000
This is the reserve of financial strength.

35:14.000 --> 35:17.000
The higher the reserve of financial strength,

35:17.000 --> 35:21.000
the better the enterprise is doing.

35:21.000 --> 35:25.000
Again, we should calculate the reserve of financial strength.

35:25.000 --> 35:33.000
And it is even better to ask to calculate it for equal periods of time.

35:33.000 --> 35:38.000
For example, once a quarter, when the financial report is submitted,

35:38.000 --> 35:43.000
we should calculate the reserve of financial strength for the economists

35:43.000 --> 35:50.000
to compare and see how the dynamics of the enterprise's financial strength changes.

35:50.000 --> 35:53.000
If it increases, it is great.

35:53.000 --> 35:56.000
It means that your enterprise feels good,

35:56.000 --> 35:59.000
and soon it will feel great.

35:59.000 --> 36:01.000
This is a reason to rejoice.

36:01.000 --> 36:05.000
If the reserve of financial strength decreases,

36:05.000 --> 36:09.000
it is a warning bell.

36:09.000 --> 36:11.000
We should pay attention to this.

36:11.000 --> 36:15.000
We should look at why the reserve of financial strength decreases.

36:15.000 --> 36:16.000
Why?

36:16.000 --> 36:19.000
Because the decrease of the reserve of financial strength

36:19.000 --> 36:26.000
means that the enterprise will feel more and more uncomfortable in the market.

36:26.000 --> 36:30.000
Once again, the higher the reserve of financial strength,

36:30.000 --> 36:34.000
the more stable the enterprise is.

36:34.000 --> 36:39.000
Moreover, the reserve of financial strength allows us to compare different enterprises.

36:39.000 --> 36:44.000
We can say which enterprise is more stable in the market, which is less stable.

36:44.000 --> 36:49.000
Stability also depends on the life of the enterprise in the market.

36:49.000 --> 36:54.000
The more stable it is, the more guarantees it has that it will exist longer and more successfully.

36:54.000 --> 36:59.000
Moreover, the reserve of financial strength is like the height of a boat.

36:59.000 --> 37:05.000
When it is still, the height of the boat does not matter.

37:05.000 --> 37:09.000
But when the waves are increasing,

37:09.000 --> 37:15.000
the boat with a small boat will soon sink and sink.

37:16.000 --> 37:20.000
And the boat with a high boat will be more stable

37:20.000 --> 37:25.000
and will be able to overcome all the obstacles that arose before it.

37:25.000 --> 37:32.000
Therefore, once again, study how the reserve of financial strength of your enterprise changes.

37:32.000 --> 37:38.000
And do everything possible to ensure that the reserve of financial strength does not decrease,

37:38.000 --> 37:43.000
but rather increases and increases.

37:45.000 --> 37:51.000
We have already discussed that when an enterprise goes through a point of profitability

37:51.000 --> 37:57.000
and starts producing more and more products,

37:57.000 --> 38:03.000
its profit starts to increase, increase, increase.

38:03.000 --> 38:09.000
And this is just great, we should be happy about it.

38:09.000 --> 38:19.000
But then we noted that such a state does not always take place.

38:19.000 --> 38:27.000
The fact is that if we look at what will happen with a very strong increase in the volume of production,

38:27.000 --> 38:31.000
we will face geometrically opposite pictures.

38:31.000 --> 38:37.000
Look carefully at the graph that is now in front of you.

38:37.000 --> 38:42.000
The area that we have just studied is located in the circle.

38:42.000 --> 38:46.000
Remember the intersection of two straight lines?

38:46.000 --> 38:49.000
Profit and total costs.

38:49.000 --> 38:54.000
What we have studied is only related to this small circle.

38:54.000 --> 38:58.000
And inside this circle, everything is fair.

38:58.000 --> 39:02.000
But look at what is changing outside this circle.

39:02.000 --> 39:04.000
How much the picture changes.

39:04.000 --> 39:10.000
Everything that happens outside the circle does not coincide with what happens inside the circle.

39:10.000 --> 39:16.000
Everything that we have just studied is related to overcoming the point of profitability.

39:16.000 --> 39:22.000
We have just crossed it and are starting to live better, better, better, to produce more.

39:22.000 --> 39:27.000
Everything is great, but it is close to the point of profitability.

39:27.000 --> 39:29.000
And what is waiting for us next?

39:30.000 --> 39:32.000
We will develop our enterprise.

39:32.000 --> 39:35.000
The enterprise will produce more and more and more products.

39:35.000 --> 39:37.000
Look, we are moving along the X axis.

39:37.000 --> 39:39.000
We are increasing the volume of production.

39:39.000 --> 39:45.000
The profit curve is significantly superior to the cost curve.

39:45.000 --> 39:48.000
And we see that the further we move along the X axis,

39:48.000 --> 39:54.000
the difference between the profit and the total costs becomes more and more and more.

39:54.000 --> 39:55.000
See?

39:56.000 --> 39:57.000
Great.

39:57.000 --> 40:01.000
The profit is increasing, increasing, increasing.

40:01.000 --> 40:06.000
But it cannot increase infinitely.

40:07.000 --> 40:09.000
And that is why.

40:09.000 --> 40:19.000
The thing is that if we increase any of the production factors,

40:20.000 --> 40:27.000
the benefit we get from increasing this production factor will increase.

40:27.000 --> 40:39.000
But the increase in the benefit we will get from increasing this factor will increase on a smaller scale.

40:39.000 --> 40:41.000
That is, it will decrease all the time.

40:42.000 --> 40:44.000
The simplest example.

40:44.000 --> 40:51.000
In a hot afternoon, you really want to drink.

40:51.000 --> 40:55.000
You drink a glass of mineral water.

40:55.000 --> 40:57.000
Very good.

40:57.000 --> 40:59.000
You completely quench your thirst.

40:59.000 --> 41:04.000
But if you pour the same second glass of mineral water in the same way,

41:04.000 --> 41:10.000
the benefit from its consumption will be less than the benefit from the first glass of water.

41:10.000 --> 41:14.000
And if you drink the third, fourth, fifth glass of water at once,

41:14.000 --> 41:27.000
the benefits of each glass of water will decrease until it becomes zero.

41:27.000 --> 41:30.000
And if you drink water even further,

41:30.000 --> 41:34.000
you will get even negative results, negative benefits.

41:34.000 --> 41:38.000
And this is good for almost everything.

41:38.000 --> 41:46.000
Consumption of any benefit, the more we consume it, the more useful it becomes.

41:46.000 --> 41:52.000
But the increase in the benefit decreases, decreases, and decreases until it becomes zero.

41:55.000 --> 41:57.000
There are only two benefits.

41:57.000 --> 42:01.000
They are considered to be insatiable thirst for power and money.

42:02.000 --> 42:08.000
And both seem to be even better.

42:08.000 --> 42:11.000
All other benefits are insatiable.

42:13.000 --> 42:25.000
And the increase in the benefit consumption always leads to the moment when further benefit consumption becomes indifferent and even harmful.

42:25.000 --> 42:29.000
We have the same thing in production.

42:32.000 --> 42:37.000
You can imagine several options for changing the production situation.

42:37.000 --> 42:47.000
For example, we change the equipment, improve the equipment, improve the main funds.

42:47.000 --> 42:51.000
We leave the rest unchanged, untouched.

42:51.000 --> 42:57.000
Imagine, our enterprise worked only in one shift, produced a certain amount of products.

42:57.000 --> 42:59.000
We change the equipment.

42:59.000 --> 43:03.000
We have now put more perfect equipment.

43:03.000 --> 43:07.000
We don't over-train the workers, we decided that we don't change anything else.

43:07.000 --> 43:09.000
More perfect equipment.

43:09.000 --> 43:15.000
Yes, more perfect equipment is more effective, it allows us to produce more products.

43:15.000 --> 43:22.000
But until our workers, whom we don't over-train, are able to work with this equipment.

43:22.000 --> 43:31.000
If we continue to change the equipment, put the most perfect machines with numerical software, which requires a very high qualification of the workers,

43:31.000 --> 43:37.000
then we will see that our workers cannot work on these machines without the appropriate increase in skill.

43:37.000 --> 43:42.000
They will stop and production will freeze.

43:42.000 --> 43:48.000
It would seem that we have put the most perfect machines, it is impossible to invent better.

43:48.000 --> 43:51.000
We cannot even produce a single product.

43:51.000 --> 44:05.000
It turns out that increasing one factor of production and investing in one factor of production not only contributes to growth,

44:05.000 --> 44:09.000
but from some point on it can stop production.

44:09.000 --> 44:13.000
This is typical for other factors of production.

44:13.000 --> 44:20.000
Let's increase the number of workers, and leave the equipment the same.

44:20.000 --> 44:27.000
For example, an enterprise that worked in one shift will be transferred to work in two shifts.

44:27.000 --> 44:30.000
We will increase the number of workers at the enterprise.

44:30.000 --> 44:33.000
From the point of view of the enterprise, this is great.

44:34.000 --> 44:43.000
Working in two shifts is very effective for the enterprise, because it allows two shifts of workers to work on the same equipment.

44:43.000 --> 44:51.000
Accordingly, the constant costs are the same, and the volume of products increases almost double.

44:51.000 --> 44:57.000
Therefore, we increase the profit that the enterprise receives.

44:57.000 --> 44:58.000
It is just great.

44:58.000 --> 45:05.000
The transition from one shift to two shifts is a very good solution for any production enterprise.

45:05.000 --> 45:09.000
Now let's try to continue this line.

45:09.000 --> 45:12.000
Let's start working in three shifts.

45:12.000 --> 45:16.000
From the point of view of equipment use, this is a positive phenomenon,

45:16.000 --> 45:22.000
because the same equipment works within one day, during three shifts.

45:22.000 --> 45:32.000
However, working in a third shift is always less effective than working in a first and second shift.

45:32.000 --> 45:41.000
The workers who work in the third shift at the enterprise, no matter how hard they try to work well,

45:41.000 --> 45:48.000
nevertheless, the body requires rest at night, physiologically.

45:48.000 --> 45:58.000
And a worker at night is not as active as he is at day time.

45:58.000 --> 46:06.000
His movements are slower, his mental abilities are even slower.

46:06.000 --> 46:13.000
Yes, a person works, but the return from him to the third shift is much less,

46:13.000 --> 46:20.000
because deep in the subconscious, a person sleeps, rests at night.

46:20.000 --> 46:25.000
This is how the human body works, he should rest at night.

46:25.000 --> 46:30.000
This is how nature has built a human life for millions of years.

46:30.000 --> 46:36.000
Therefore, in the third shift we always have a lower productivity of labor.

46:36.000 --> 46:43.000
Moreover, a worker in the third shift needs to rest more, to take more breaks.

46:43.000 --> 46:49.000
Moreover, it should be noted that there are always fewer people who want to work in the third shift

46:49.000 --> 46:53.000
than those who want to work in the first and second shifts.

46:53.000 --> 46:58.000
And if there are fewer people who want to work, then to attract them to work,

46:58.000 --> 47:03.000
workers in the third shift need to pay more wages.

47:03.000 --> 47:11.000
We see that there is less production, and the pay in the third shift is higher.

47:11.000 --> 47:18.000
Therefore, the economic efficiency of the enterprise in the third shift is lower than in the first shift.

47:18.000 --> 47:29.000
Thus, wanting to improve the situation, we go from one shift to two, and see significant improvements,

47:29.000 --> 47:34.000
and we go to work in the third shift and see a slowdown.

47:34.000 --> 47:40.000
The third shift does not give the same growth as, for example, the second shift.

47:40.000 --> 47:44.000
The third shift is less effective.

47:44.000 --> 47:50.000
Let's not increase the number of workers, let's increase their qualifications.

47:50.000 --> 47:53.000
Let's approach this issue from the third side.

47:53.000 --> 47:57.000
We have the simplest equipment that workers use.

47:57.000 --> 48:02.000
And the workers cope with it perfectly.

48:02.000 --> 48:09.000
Let's not change the equipment, the simplest thing, let's start to increase the qualifications.

48:09.000 --> 48:17.000
Instead of unqualified workers, let's take workers from the technical school qualification.

48:17.000 --> 48:23.000
These workers are more qualified, they have theory and practice,

48:23.000 --> 48:29.000
they have better skills than unqualified workers who just came from the street,

48:29.000 --> 48:35.000
who have been entrusted with equipment, and who can harm this equipment more than use it.

48:35.000 --> 48:39.000
And qualified workers are a completely different matter.

48:39.000 --> 48:45.000
Therefore, the increase in the qualification of the work used instead of unqualified workers,

48:45.000 --> 48:48.000
there is a positive phenomenon.

48:48.000 --> 48:53.000
That's why enterprises always look for workers of higher qualifications.

48:53.000 --> 48:57.000
But we continue to move in this direction.

48:57.000 --> 49:07.000
And instead of qualified workers, we will take and offer this job to a qualified worker with a higher education.

49:07.000 --> 49:10.000
And here we have the first call.

49:10.000 --> 49:15.000
On the one hand, a qualified worker with a higher education has theory.

49:15.000 --> 49:21.000
If he studied well and listened to the lectures we are listening to now.

49:21.000 --> 49:29.000
He has higher knowledge than a worker, even a qualified one, I mean theoretical knowledge.

49:29.000 --> 49:42.000
But a worker of a higher education has more emphasis on theoretical knowledge than on practical knowledge.

49:42.000 --> 49:46.000
Unlike a worker who graduated from a technical school.

49:46.000 --> 49:53.000
And that's why this worker has theoretical knowledge, but to a lesser extent he has practical skills.

49:53.000 --> 50:03.000
That's why when graduates of the universities come and start working for the first time in their lives at enterprises,

50:03.000 --> 50:12.000
they have to study a lot, to learn, to gain those skills of practical experience that no institute can give them.

50:12.000 --> 50:15.000
But that's not the task of the institute.

50:15.000 --> 50:19.000
The task of the institute is to give theoretical skills, first of all.

50:19.000 --> 50:22.000
Well, and practical skills, but still, first of all, theoretical skills.

50:22.000 --> 50:28.000
And if we start to raise our level further, and instead of workers who have just graduated from the institute,

50:28.000 --> 50:32.000
we'll start to invite people who have a very high theoretical education.

50:32.000 --> 50:36.000
Candidates to science, PhD students, academics.

50:36.000 --> 50:43.000
We'll invite them to work and say, here's a hammer, here's a chisel, dear academics, let's work.

50:43.000 --> 50:47.000
What will be our return?

50:47.000 --> 50:51.000
Do you think our efficiency will increase from such work or decrease?

50:52.000 --> 50:57.000
Yes, dear academics have a huge amount of knowledge.

50:57.000 --> 51:06.000
But, to be honest, there are probably some academics who have held a chisel and hammer only in their childhood.

51:06.000 --> 51:15.000
And to say that they can do a great job of work that a worker should do, you can doubt that.

51:16.000 --> 51:18.000
But that's not all.

51:18.000 --> 51:28.000
The salary of the academics is, of course, higher than that of those who don't have such a high scientific qualification.

51:28.000 --> 51:34.000
Consequently, fewer skills in work and higher salary.

51:34.000 --> 51:41.000
Thus, we see that further increase in the qualification of a worker leads to a decrease in the efficiency of its use.

51:42.000 --> 51:49.000
Any factor of production that we don't take, if we increase it,

51:49.000 --> 51:56.000
only this factor increases, it leads to a decrease in the efficiency of production.

51:56.000 --> 52:04.000
At first it grows, then the growth stops, and then there's a decrease. Always.

52:04.000 --> 52:08.000
What should be done to prevent this from happening?

52:09.000 --> 52:11.000
The answer is simple.

52:11.000 --> 52:14.000
Change the factors in a complex way.

52:14.000 --> 52:20.000
If we increase the qualification of a worker, then we change the equipment together with him.

52:20.000 --> 52:26.000
Or vice versa, if we increase the equipment, we put a better one, we increase the qualification of the worker.

52:26.000 --> 52:31.000
If we put the machines with numerical software instead of the usual machines,

52:31.000 --> 52:37.000
then the workers who should work for these machines should have a higher qualification.

52:37.000 --> 52:43.000
Then the equipment and the workers will correspond to each other.

52:43.000 --> 52:47.000
And the production will grow and not decrease.

52:49.000 --> 52:53.000
But this is regarding the use of equipment and workers.

52:53.000 --> 53:01.000
As for, for example, the work in the third shift, here, unfortunately, we will get a decrease anyway.

53:01.000 --> 53:07.000
Because it's impossible to make a person who would live only in the night,

53:07.000 --> 53:11.000
he needs to completely rebuild himself and live only in the night,

53:11.000 --> 53:15.000
which is unlikely to be interesting for the workers themselves.

53:15.000 --> 53:19.000
After all, a person is a daily being.

53:21.000 --> 53:30.000
Thus, we have seen that the change of production factors in enterprises is rather ambiguous.

53:30.000 --> 53:36.000
It's impossible to say that if we improve the production factor, then we will have a cloudless life in the future.

53:36.000 --> 53:39.000
No, it's a very subtle question.

53:39.000 --> 53:43.000
Here, it's possible to improve the production factor.

53:43.000 --> 53:45.000
It's certainly so.

53:45.000 --> 53:49.000
We need to look at how the costs are increasing.

53:49.000 --> 53:55.000
If the volume of production grows faster than the costs,

53:55.000 --> 54:06.000
that is, the growth of the production volume in the unit of production grows faster than the growth of the costs in the unit of production,

54:06.000 --> 54:10.000
then we have a positive phenomenon in the economy.

54:10.000 --> 54:15.000
We have an increase in the profits for the enterprise.

54:15.000 --> 54:23.000
But if the growth of the revenue volume grows slower than the growth of the costs,

54:23.000 --> 54:26.000
then we have a reverse picture.

54:26.000 --> 54:31.000
The costs grow faster than the revenue volume, and the profit value decreases.

54:31.000 --> 54:36.000
This is exactly what the graph you see in front of you is reflecting.

54:36.000 --> 54:39.000
Now, pay attention to this graph.

54:39.000 --> 54:46.000
We are already moving away from what is depicted in the left part and moving to the middle of this graph.

54:46.000 --> 54:47.000
Look carefully.

54:47.000 --> 54:55.000
If an enterprise produces a product equal to x2, then we have the largest maximum profit.

54:55.000 --> 55:04.000
It is at this point that the revenue in relation to costs, the difference between revenue and costs, is the highest.

55:05.000 --> 55:09.000
This is the ideal point for production.

55:09.000 --> 55:15.000
Any businessman should know this point for his enterprise.

55:15.000 --> 55:23.000
This is the point of production where the maximum profit in relation to the unit of production is the highest.

55:23.000 --> 55:25.000
This is a very important point.

55:25.000 --> 55:29.000
The thing is that if we work to the left or to the right of this point,

55:29.000 --> 55:32.000
that is, we will produce more or less products,

55:32.000 --> 55:36.000
we will get less profit in relation to the unit of production.

55:36.000 --> 55:38.000
We will work to the left.

55:38.000 --> 55:42.000
Yes, the enterprise will work at full capacity, but there will be no profit.

55:42.000 --> 55:47.000
And it is at this point that the profit from the unit of production is the highest.

55:47.000 --> 55:50.000
This is the point that we need to find.

55:51.000 --> 55:59.000
Therefore, it is high time to stop listening to lectures, call an economist and give him a task.

55:59.000 --> 56:07.000
Find out the point at which the maximum profit will be produced at the enterprise.

56:07.000 --> 56:14.000
And then compare the real point at which your enterprise is located with this point of maximum profit.

56:14.000 --> 56:17.000
Look where you are.

56:17.000 --> 56:19.000
To the left or to the right?

56:19.000 --> 56:22.000
How far are you from the point of maximum profit?

56:22.000 --> 56:27.000
The thing is that if you are to the left, you need to increase the volume of production.

56:27.000 --> 56:33.000
And then you will reach the level where you will get the maximum profit per unit of production.

56:33.000 --> 56:34.000
Attention!

56:34.000 --> 56:36.000
There is a very important point here.

56:36.000 --> 56:43.000
You should not only produce the product, but also sell it.

56:43.000 --> 56:49.000
Otherwise, it will be in your warehouse and will cause even more harm than if you did not produce this product.

56:49.000 --> 56:55.000
Therefore, before making a decision that you need to increase the volume of production,

56:55.000 --> 57:00.000
you need to invite a marketologist and give him a task.

57:00.000 --> 57:07.000
Find out whether we can implement a larger volume of production of our product on the market.

57:07.000 --> 57:10.000
Will the market accept this product?

57:10.000 --> 57:12.000
This is a very serious question.

57:12.000 --> 57:17.000
There are other competitors on the market who produce this product.

57:17.000 --> 57:21.000
This is an important question.

57:21.000 --> 57:27.000
If the marketologist answers that the market will accept this product, the market is not saturated,

57:27.000 --> 57:33.000
you can boldly set the task to increase the volume of production and increase production to the value of X2,

57:33.000 --> 57:38.000
to the point where the maximum profit per unit of production is.

57:38.000 --> 57:40.000
You can boldly follow this path.

57:40.000 --> 57:44.000
This is the right path to the development of the enterprise.

57:44.000 --> 57:48.000
And if the marketologist says no,

57:48.000 --> 57:54.000
unfortunately, we are already producing the maximum amount of products that the market can accept.

57:54.000 --> 57:58.000
This is a completely different question.

57:58.000 --> 58:06.000
This means that further increase in the number of produced products is not feasible.

58:06.000 --> 58:09.000
Otherwise, the product will be all in the warehouse.

58:09.000 --> 58:13.000
Yes, the profit per unit of production is less,

58:13.000 --> 58:18.000
but this is the maximum that can be achieved in these conditions.

58:18.000 --> 58:21.000
Here you need to look at the question more broadly.

58:21.000 --> 58:26.000
Can we increase the volume of production if we reduce the price?

58:26.000 --> 58:31.000
This will be the second task for the marketologist.

58:31.000 --> 58:36.000
The fact is that the reduction of the price leads to a reduction in profit,

58:36.000 --> 58:42.000
but the movement to the point X2 leads to an increase in profit.

58:42.000 --> 58:46.000
What is more, will the profit be reduced from the reduction of the price,

58:46.000 --> 58:50.000
or will the profit be increased due to the increase in the volume of production?

58:50.000 --> 58:53.000
Here you need to compare, you need to look carefully.

58:53.000 --> 58:57.000
If we get more profit from increasing the volume of production,

58:57.000 --> 59:01.000
and if we give part of it to the consumer due to the reduction of the price,

59:01.000 --> 59:06.000
then this is the right way to move to the enterprise.

59:06.000 --> 59:12.000
But if during the calculation it turns out that the volume of production,

59:12.000 --> 59:17.000
which characterizes your enterprise, is to the right of the point X2,

59:17.000 --> 59:20.000
the maximum profit per unit of production,

59:20.000 --> 59:24.000
then the situation is diametrically opposite.

59:24.000 --> 59:31.000
I would like to draw your attention to the fact that here you cannot increase the volume of production.

59:31.000 --> 59:37.000
It would seem logical that the more you produce, the better,

59:37.000 --> 59:40.000
but in fact this is not the case at all.

59:40.000 --> 59:43.000
I would even say that this is absolutely not the case.

59:43.000 --> 59:50.000
The fact is that the amount of profit per unit of production is reduced.

59:51.000 --> 59:57.000
Therefore, if you are to the right of the point of the maximum profit per unit of production,

59:57.000 --> 01:00:03.000
then you have two options.

01:00:03.000 --> 01:00:08.000
Now we will talk about them in the story.

01:00:08.000 --> 01:00:12.000
The first option is seen on the graph.

01:00:12.000 --> 01:00:16.000
This is, of course, to shift to the left to the point X2,

01:00:16.000 --> 01:00:18.000
that is, to reduce the volume of production.

01:00:18.000 --> 01:00:21.000
No matter how paradoxical it may seem,

01:00:21.000 --> 01:00:25.000
you need to reduce the volume of production to get profit,

01:00:25.000 --> 01:00:29.000
rather than increase the volume of production so as not to get this profit.

01:00:29.000 --> 01:00:34.000
After all, if we shift further, for example, to the point X3 on the graph,

01:00:34.000 --> 01:00:36.000
it would seem that we have increased the volume of production,

01:00:36.000 --> 01:00:39.000
we have become so good, but the profit is zero.

01:00:39.000 --> 01:00:43.000
The meaning of our existence is zero.

01:00:44.000 --> 01:00:51.000
In this case, of course, shifting to the left to the point X2,

01:00:51.000 --> 01:00:57.000
where the maximum profit per unit of production is reduced, is more logical.

01:00:57.000 --> 01:01:02.000
You will say, but we want to increase the volume of production,

01:01:02.000 --> 01:01:04.000
we want to expand our enterprise.

01:01:04.000 --> 01:01:07.000
How can we do this? Why can't we increase the volume of production?

01:01:07.000 --> 01:01:12.000
Well, why can't we increase the volume of production at this enterprise is already clear,

01:01:12.000 --> 01:01:17.000
but how to increase the volume of production in general is a separate conversation.

01:01:17.000 --> 01:01:21.000
The fact is that what we are talking about

01:01:21.000 --> 01:01:28.000
characterizes this plant or this workshop or this site for the production of products.

01:01:28.000 --> 01:01:34.000
But if there is a second such plant or site next to it,

01:01:34.000 --> 01:01:38.000
also tuned for the optimal volume of production,

01:01:38.000 --> 01:01:42.000
then in total they will produce twice as much production.

01:01:42.000 --> 01:01:47.000
At the same time, each of these sites will be tuned for the optimal regime.

01:01:47.000 --> 01:01:49.000
This is a very important point.

01:01:49.000 --> 01:01:53.000
By printing the optimal regimes,

01:01:53.000 --> 01:01:57.000
the second site, the third, the fourth, the fifth,

01:01:57.000 --> 01:02:01.000
spreading them all over the country, all over the globe.

01:02:01.000 --> 01:02:04.000
Pay attention to how McDonald's works.

01:02:04.000 --> 01:02:08.000
McDonald's has not created the only one establishment

01:02:08.000 --> 01:02:12.000
from which Big Macs are brought all over the globe.

01:02:12.000 --> 01:02:20.000
No. McDonald's creates points similar to each other all over the globe.

01:02:20.000 --> 01:02:24.000
As a result, each point is tuned for the optimal regime

01:02:24.000 --> 01:02:28.000
and in total they give a huge amount of products

01:02:28.000 --> 01:02:31.000
in the optimal regime in terms of profit.

01:02:32.000 --> 01:02:36.000
This is much better than if there was only one McDonald's

01:02:36.000 --> 01:02:38.000
for the whole globe.

01:02:38.000 --> 01:02:40.000
The same is true here.

01:02:40.000 --> 01:02:45.000
If we have found the optimal production regime for our enterprise,

01:02:45.000 --> 01:02:49.000
then the next step is to copy this production.

01:02:49.000 --> 01:02:53.000
Remember the example of McDonald's and decide to move in this direction.

01:02:53.000 --> 01:02:57.000
Build a second workshop next to it, a third workshop, a fourth workshop.

01:02:57.000 --> 01:02:59.000
You can build them next to each other.

01:02:59.000 --> 01:03:02.000
You can open branches in other cities.

01:03:02.000 --> 01:03:05.000
These are all issues of the same order.

01:03:05.000 --> 01:03:09.000
The most important thing is that each production site

01:03:09.000 --> 01:03:14.000
will be optimally tuned and will bring you the maximum profit

01:03:14.000 --> 01:03:18.000
per unit of the produced product.

01:03:18.000 --> 01:03:22.000
This is a very important point.

01:03:23.000 --> 01:03:30.000
This regime has its own name.

01:03:30.000 --> 01:03:34.000
It is called the American business regime.

01:03:34.000 --> 01:03:40.000
It is believed that all American enterprises work in the regime

01:03:40.000 --> 01:03:44.000
of the maximum profit per unit of production.

01:03:44.000 --> 01:03:47.000
But this is not the only regime.

01:03:47.000 --> 01:03:51.000
As I told you today that you can move from the point to the right of X2

01:03:51.000 --> 01:03:53.000
in two different directions,

01:03:53.000 --> 01:03:57.000
I meant that there is another possible direction of movement.

01:04:00.000 --> 01:04:04.000
If we are interested in profit,

01:04:04.000 --> 01:04:11.000
we are interested in its absolute maximum amount.

01:04:11.000 --> 01:04:14.000
What happens in this case?

01:04:15.000 --> 01:04:20.000
The absolute amount of profit is the product of the profit per unit of production

01:04:20.000 --> 01:04:23.000
multiplied by the number of produced products.

01:04:26.000 --> 01:04:28.000
Is this question clear?

01:04:28.000 --> 01:04:32.000
The conclusion is that the maximum amount of profit

01:04:32.000 --> 01:04:38.000
can be obtained by the optimal combination of these two quantities,

01:04:38.000 --> 01:04:41.000
the profit per unit of production and the number of produced products.

01:04:41.000 --> 01:04:44.000
You can not have the maximum profit per unit of production,

01:04:44.000 --> 01:04:47.000
but have such a large number of products

01:04:47.000 --> 01:04:53.000
that their products will give the largest amount of profit.

01:04:55.000 --> 01:04:58.000
This regime was called the Japanese regime.

01:04:58.000 --> 01:05:03.000
It is assumed that Japanese enterprises work in this regime.

01:05:03.000 --> 01:05:07.000
They get the maximum profit,

01:05:08.000 --> 01:05:13.000
but the profit per unit of production is not the maximum.

01:05:14.000 --> 01:05:19.000
The work in this regime means the production of a huge amount of products.

01:05:20.000 --> 01:05:23.000
Yes, the profit per unit of production is reduced.

01:05:23.000 --> 01:05:27.000
Look, this point, which characterizes the Japanese production process,

01:05:27.000 --> 01:05:30.000
is to the right of X2 on our graph.

01:05:30.000 --> 01:05:35.000
Yes, the profit per unit of production will be 10% less.

01:05:36.000 --> 01:05:41.000
And the production volume will be 50% more.

01:05:44.000 --> 01:05:49.000
The production of these two quantities will give more than we had in X2.

01:05:53.000 --> 01:05:57.000
That is, working in this second regime, the Japanese production regime,

01:05:57.000 --> 01:06:01.000
gives the maximum profit for the enterprise.

01:06:02.000 --> 01:06:07.000
Yes, the profit per unit of production is very small.

01:06:08.000 --> 01:06:11.000
But the value of this profit is huge.

01:06:11.000 --> 01:06:16.000
It is the maximum amount of products that can be obtained at this enterprise.

01:06:17.000 --> 01:06:20.000
If you work in the first regime,

01:06:20.000 --> 01:06:24.000
you need to distribute these products to the workshops,

01:06:24.000 --> 01:06:28.000
to the plots, all over the country, all over the globe.

01:06:29.000 --> 01:06:34.000
Working in the second regime does not mean that you will be distributed.

01:06:34.000 --> 01:06:39.000
It means that the maximum profit will be taken from this enterprise.

01:06:39.000 --> 01:06:43.000
The profit that can be obtained at this enterprise.

01:06:44.000 --> 01:06:47.000
Maybe it is a transition to two shifts.

01:06:47.000 --> 01:06:50.000
Maybe it is some other technical solution.

01:06:50.000 --> 01:06:55.000
But the maximum profit will be the total profit of this enterprise.

01:06:56.000 --> 01:07:02.000
There is a version of why these two regimes of work appeared.

01:07:02.000 --> 01:07:07.000
Some countries work in one regime, and some countries work in another regime.

01:07:07.000 --> 01:07:10.000
This version states the following.

01:07:11.000 --> 01:07:14.000
The regime that is called the American regime,

01:07:14.000 --> 01:07:17.000
that is, the maximum profit per unit of production,

01:07:17.000 --> 01:07:23.000
is more characteristic for those countries where the territory allows to build new factories.

01:07:23.000 --> 01:07:26.000
There is no problem with the land.

01:07:26.000 --> 01:07:29.000
You can build many factories.

01:07:29.000 --> 01:07:32.000
The country is huge, there is a lot of space.

01:07:32.000 --> 01:07:37.000
You can easily build new buildings, new workshops.

01:07:38.000 --> 01:07:39.000
And vice versa.

01:07:39.000 --> 01:07:44.000
In small countries, where each piece of land is worth gold,

01:07:44.000 --> 01:07:50.000
where it is very difficult to build another workshop, another factory,

01:07:51.000 --> 01:07:58.000
there they try to make the maximum profit from the factory that has already been built.

01:08:00.000 --> 01:08:03.000
Japan is the best example of this.

01:08:05.000 --> 01:08:06.000
Look at the map.

01:08:06.000 --> 01:08:10.000
Compare Russia with Japan in terms of territory.

01:08:11.000 --> 01:08:12.000
They are incomparable.

01:08:13.000 --> 01:08:18.000
Now imagine that Japan has almost the same population as Russia.

01:08:18.000 --> 01:08:25.000
This small country on the map has almost the same population as Russia.

01:08:26.000 --> 01:08:31.000
Not to mention that the production volume in Japan is colossal.

01:08:33.000 --> 01:08:36.000
The land in Japan is worth gold.

01:08:36.000 --> 01:08:43.000
Maybe that's why the way to make the maximum profit from the factory,

01:08:44.000 --> 01:08:49.000
from the enterprise, from the land where the products are produced, is very difficult.

01:08:49.000 --> 01:08:54.000
This regime is characterized by the production of a huge amount of products.

01:08:55.000 --> 01:09:00.000
If in the first regime, when the maximum profit is one unit,

01:09:01.000 --> 01:09:03.000
you don't need to produce a lot of products,

01:09:04.000 --> 01:09:06.000
you need to produce the optimal amount of them,

01:09:06.000 --> 01:09:10.000
then in the second regime you need to produce the maximum amount of products.

01:09:10.000 --> 01:09:15.000
That's why Japan is famous for the huge amount of produced products.

01:09:16.000 --> 01:09:22.000
With such a huge amount, it is inevitable to develop the foreign market,

01:09:23.000 --> 01:09:25.000
with export to all countries of the world,

01:09:26.000 --> 01:09:29.000
because this is inevitable in this regime of work.

01:09:32.000 --> 01:09:34.000
We have compared two regimes.

01:09:34.000 --> 01:09:36.000
It is appropriate to ask now,

01:09:36.000 --> 01:09:42.000
which regime of work do our Russian enterprises work in?

01:09:43.000 --> 01:09:45.000
As an owner of an enterprise,

01:09:45.000 --> 01:09:47.000
who is listening to this lecture now,

01:09:47.000 --> 01:09:50.000
think and answer yourself the question,

01:09:50.000 --> 01:09:55.000
which regime of work is more suitable for us, Russian businessmen,

01:09:55.000 --> 01:09:58.000
the American or the Japanese?

01:09:59.000 --> 01:10:00.000
What are we striving for?

01:10:00.000 --> 01:10:03.000
To get the maximum profit from a single produced product

01:10:03.000 --> 01:10:06.000
or to get the maximum profit from an enterprise?

01:10:06.000 --> 01:10:10.000
When I asked this question to other listeners at my lectures,

01:10:10.000 --> 01:10:12.000
to the owners of enterprises,

01:10:12.000 --> 01:10:15.000
who were listening to these lectures,

01:10:16.000 --> 01:10:18.000
they all answered me in one voice,

01:10:18.000 --> 01:10:20.000
that the American path is closer to them.

01:10:21.000 --> 01:10:26.000
They say that every Russian enterprise is set up

01:10:26.000 --> 01:10:30.000
to get the maximum profit from a single produced product.

01:10:30.000 --> 01:10:33.000
But then I ask them the following question,

01:10:33.000 --> 01:10:35.000
if this path is closer to us,

01:10:35.000 --> 01:10:39.000
please tell me, do you market this production?

01:10:40.000 --> 01:10:42.000
And they answer, no.

01:10:42.000 --> 01:10:44.000
Unfortunately, in our country,

01:10:44.000 --> 01:10:50.000
the issue of marketing production is not so simple.

01:10:51.000 --> 01:10:53.000
It is not so easy for our businessmen

01:10:53.000 --> 01:10:57.000
to open many branches all over the country.

01:10:57.000 --> 01:10:59.000
It is a difficult issue.

01:10:59.000 --> 01:11:02.000
Probably, in the USA it is easier to solve

01:11:02.000 --> 01:11:05.000
if this method has received a similar name

01:11:05.000 --> 01:11:08.000
and is more difficult for this country.

01:11:08.000 --> 01:11:14.000
I would like for our business to be easier to develop branches,

01:11:14.000 --> 01:11:17.000
to create enterprises all over the country,

01:11:17.000 --> 01:11:20.000
since our business is also struggling to get the maximum profit from a single produced product.

01:11:21.000 --> 01:11:25.000
Then we will get the maximum profit from a single produced product

01:11:25.000 --> 01:11:28.000
and the maximum profit from a single produced product

01:11:29.000 --> 01:11:31.000
that is widespread, concentrated,

01:11:31.000 --> 01:11:37.000
closer to the consumer in all corners of the country and the world.

01:11:37.000 --> 01:11:39.000
This is a very important point.

01:11:39.000 --> 01:11:41.000
This is a very important point.

01:11:41.000 --> 01:11:44.000
And before we move on,

01:11:44.000 --> 01:11:48.000
you should think again about how your enterprise works,

01:11:48.000 --> 01:11:53.000
what production mode is more optimal for your enterprise.

01:11:53.000 --> 01:11:56.000
If you can market your products,

01:11:56.000 --> 01:11:59.000
open a new branch, a new plot,

01:11:59.000 --> 01:12:05.000
then the way to get the maximum profit from a single produced product is more acceptable.

01:12:05.000 --> 01:12:09.000
But if you cannot do this for one reason or another,

01:12:09.000 --> 01:12:11.000
lack of capital,

01:12:11.000 --> 01:12:16.000
inability to get permission to build a new enterprise,

01:12:16.000 --> 01:12:21.000
then the way is more Japanese.

01:12:21.000 --> 01:12:28.000
Then you should try to get the maximum profit from this enterprise.

01:12:30.000 --> 01:12:32.000
But you should not forget once again

01:12:34.000 --> 01:12:38.000
that as soon as we move along the way of increasing production volume,

01:12:38.000 --> 01:12:42.000
we should agree on this issue with marketologists.

01:12:44.000 --> 01:12:47.000
Will we be able to implement this product?

01:12:47.000 --> 01:12:51.000
If we increase production volume in several times,

01:12:51.000 --> 01:12:56.000
it is not a fact that we can easily implement this product.

01:12:56.000 --> 01:13:00.000
It is not a coincidence that these enterprises are concentrated all over the country,

01:13:00.000 --> 01:13:03.000
that is, they are closer to the consumers.

01:13:03.000 --> 01:13:08.000
Because to import a product from one point to all corners of the globe

01:13:08.000 --> 01:13:13.000
is less effective than if production is concentrated all over the globe.

01:13:13.000 --> 01:13:15.000
Remember McDonald's.

01:13:15.000 --> 01:13:18.000
Imagine a McDonald's point

01:13:18.000 --> 01:13:22.000
with Big Macs all over the globe.

01:13:22.000 --> 01:13:27.000
You come in, order a meal, and wait for Big Macs to be delivered to you from the USA.

01:13:27.000 --> 01:13:30.000
And you do not leave the cafe until it is delivered to you.

01:13:30.000 --> 01:13:34.000
This is what the right production regime means.

01:13:34.000 --> 01:13:39.000
To concentrate production or to produce at one point.

01:13:39.000 --> 01:13:43.000
To produce the maximum profit from a single product

01:13:43.000 --> 01:13:48.000
or to produce the maximum profit from the whole enterprise.

01:13:49.000 --> 01:13:52.000
Each of you, businessmen,

01:13:52.000 --> 01:13:55.000
current businessmen or those who are going to become businessmen,

01:13:55.000 --> 01:13:58.000
because if you are studying MBA,

01:13:58.000 --> 01:14:01.000
it means that you are ready to advance in business.

01:14:01.000 --> 01:14:04.000
It is possible that in the future

01:14:04.000 --> 01:14:07.000
each of you will become an owner of an enterprise,

01:14:07.000 --> 01:14:09.000
who will manage the enterprise.

01:14:09.000 --> 01:14:11.000
And you need to solve this issue for yourself.

01:14:11.000 --> 01:14:14.000
How will your enterprise develop?

01:14:14.000 --> 01:14:18.000
Where is the strategic line of development of your enterprise?

01:14:18.000 --> 01:14:23.000
What do you want to get from your enterprise in terms of economy?

01:14:24.000 --> 01:14:26.000
These are the most important questions.

01:14:26.000 --> 01:14:29.000
And this graph that you see on the screen now,

01:14:29.000 --> 01:14:33.000
you should remember it very carefully for the rest of your life.

01:14:33.000 --> 01:14:38.000
